  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Corruption\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Prevention Methods:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Asset freezing and seizure mechanisms\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Business license revocation\n- Personal liability for executives\n\n5. Global Cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Cross-border investigation support\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different financial systems and jurisdictions.",
